      "I've always seen currency as more than just a tool for transactions—it's fundamentally a promise. A promise between people, between communities, and across generations that the value you earn, save, and exchange today will hold true tomorrow. In traditional fiat systems, that promise has been broken time and again through inflation, overprinting, and centralized control. As the founder of TEXITcoin, I created TXC to restore that broken promise and deliver a currency that's truly honest, reliable, and rooted in trust.",
      "At its core, every currency is a social contract: \"I accept this in payment because I believe others will accept it from me later, at roughly the same value.\" When that belief erodes—when governments print endlessly, devalue savings, or favor insiders—the entire system frays. Fiat money's promise becomes hollow, eroded by hidden taxes on purchasing power and manipulated issuance. We've all felt it: wages that don't keep up, savings that shrink, and the constant grind of rising costs despite hard work.",
      "Cryptocurrency was born to fix this. Bitcoin showed the world that money could be a verifiable promise enforced by code, not by decree—scarce, transparent, and immutable. But many projects drifted from that ideal, introducing pre-mines, centralized control, or inflationary mechanics that echoed the very problems they aimed to solve.",
      "TEXITcoin recommits to the pure promise of sound money. It's not just another token; it's a Layer-1 blockchain designed from the ground up as a promise kept:",
      "This is the essence of honest money: a currency that keeps its word. It rewards productivity, preserves wealth across time, and empowers individuals rather than extracting from them. In TEXITcoin, the promise isn't marketing fluff—it's enforced by mathematics, secured by the network, and upheld by a community committed to long-term integrity.",
