      "Gold was the currency of royalty, silver for the gentry, copper for everyday transactions. These metals remained the cornerstone of commerce for centuries. Then came paper money — a claim ticket on those metals, eventually severed from them entirely. In just the last hundred years, the pace of change has accelerated dramatically.",
      "Today money is more abstract than ever. Venmo, Zelle, and Cash App move value instantly with no physical exchange. But the true revolution is cryptocurrency. Bitcoin operates without a central authority — a peer-to-peer network verifying transactions through cryptography, with a fixed and finite supply. That's a fundamentally different kind of money than anything that came before it.",
